{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778980259156,"sessionID":"ses_1cc8399e9ffe5MJ58juVe42pjM","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_iUIyDyoIiPhFk2UJYQtl9AyW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json","offset":1,"limit":400},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"body\": \"3 imported terms are unsatisfiable due violations of taxon constraints:\\nFMA:77600\\nZFA:0000497\\nZFA:0000592\\n\\nSolution proposed by @gouttegd in #3592 \\n\\nFor the first one (FMA:77600), I think the problematic axiom is\\n\\n'[epiphyseal tract](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0034714)' EquivalentTo '[cranial neuron projection bundle](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0034713)' and ([innervates](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002134) some '[parietal organ](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0004869)')\\n\\nThat innervates bit seems too precise. The parietal organ is only a part of the '[pineal complex](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0015238)' (a part that does not exist in mammals), but the '[pineal tract](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0034715)' (a branching part of the epiphyseal tract) innervates another part of the pineal complex, the '[pineal body](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001905)'.\\n\\nSo if a branch of the epiphyseal tract innervates a distinct part of the pineal complex, then the entire epiphyseal tract clearly innervates more than just the parietal organ.\\n\\nI believe the axiom should be\\n\\n'[epiphyseal tract](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0034714)' EquivalentTo '[cranial neuron projection bundle](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0034713)' and ([innervates](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002134) some '[pineal complex](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0015238)')\\n\\nAs for the other two (the ZFA ones), I think the problem lies with the '[adductor muscle of hip](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0011144)'.\\n\\nThat term is logically defined as\\n\\n'[adductor muscle of hip](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0011144)' EquivalentTo '[adductor muscle](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0011145)' and ('[part of](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050)' some '[pelvic complex](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0010709)')\\n\\nbut is also explicitly classified as\\n\\n'[adductor muscl... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n3:   \"comments\": [],\n4:   \"title\": \"Revise lofical definition causing violations of taxon constraints\",\n5:   \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3596\"\n6: }\n\n(End of file - total 6 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"body\": \"3 imported terms are unsatisfiable due violations of taxon constraints:\\nFMA:77600\\nZFA:0000497\\nZFA:0000592\\n\\nSolution proposed by @gouttegd in #3592 \\n\\nFor the first one (FMA:77600), I think the problematic axiom is\\n\\n'[epiphyseal tract](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0034714)' EquivalentTo '[cranial neuron projection bundle](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0034713)' and ([innervates](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002134) some '[parietal organ](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0004869)')\\n\\nThat innervates bit seems too precise. The parietal organ is only a part of the '[pineal complex](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0015238)' (a part that does not exist in mammals), but the '[pineal tract](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0034715)' (a branching part of the epiphyseal tract) innervates another part of the pineal complex, the '[pineal body](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001905)'.\\n\\nSo if a branch of the epiphyseal tract innervates a distinct part of the pineal complex, then the entire epiphyseal tract clearly innervates more than just the parietal organ.\\n\\nI believe the axiom should be\\n\\n'[epiphyseal tract](http://purl.obolib