{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778980423764,"sessionID":"ses_1cc8399e9ffe5MJ58juVe42pjM","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_jRZTIogpT1OBN5hitFRygLVS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+I revised the logical definition of `epiphyseal tract` to target `pineal complex` rather than `parietal organ`, and removed the generic `innervated_by obturator nerve` restriction from `adductor muscle of hip` to avoid propagating tetrapod-specific constraints to broader vertebrate imports.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+Resolved issue #3596 by making two targeted ontology edits to remove taxon-constraint conflicts affecting imported FMA and ZFA terms.\n+\n+Changes made:\n+- Updated `UBERON:0034714` `epiphyseal tract` so its text definition and equivalence axiom use `innervates some UBERON:0015238 ! pineal complex` instead of `parietal organ`.\n+- Removed the generic `relationship: innervated_by UBERON:0005465 ! obturator nerve` axiom from `UBERON:0011144` `adductor muscle of hip`.\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- The issue discussion pointed out that the epiphyseal tract includes branches innervating distinct parts of the pineal complex, so restricting the whole tract to the parietal organ was too narrow and caused the FMA import to violate taxon constraints.\n+- `adductor muscle of hip` had a broad logical definition (`adductor muscle` that is `part_of` some `pelvic complex`) but also carried a tetrapod-specific obturator nerve classification. That combination overconstrained descendant imported teleost classes such as `pelvic adductor profundus` and `superficial pelvic adductor`.\n+\n+Validation performed:\n+- Checked out and edited only the affected UBERON terms via `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl`.\n+- Reserialized `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` with `robot convert`.\n+- Ran `robot reason --input src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo --reasoner ELK --output /tmp/opencode/issue-3596-reasoned.owl` successfully.\n+- Re-verified the final checked-in stanzas for `UBERON:0034714` and `UBERON:0011144`.\n+\n+Completed checklist:\n+- [x] Read imported issue context\n+- [x] Inspected referenced UBERON terms and related structures\n+- [x] Applied minimal logical-definition fixes\n+- [x] Checked changes back into `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`\n+- [x] Reserialized the ontology\n+- [x] Ran reasoner validation\n+- [x] Committed only the ontology file change locally\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,3 @@\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+I revised the logical definition of `epiphyseal tract` to target `pineal complex` rather than `parietal organ`, and removed the generic `innervated_by obturator nerve` restriction from `adductor muscle of hip` to avoid propagating tetrapod-specific constraints to broader vertebrate imports.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,24 @@\n+Resolved issue #3596 by making two targeted ontology edits to remove taxon-constraint conflicts affecting imported FMA and ZFA terms.\n+\n+Changes made:\n+- Updated `UBERON:0034714` `epiphyseal tract` so its text definition and equivalence axiom use `innervates some UBERON:0015238 ! pineal complex` instead of `parietal organ`.\n+- Removed the generic `relationship: