{"type":"text","timestamp":1778980437702,"sessionID":"ses_1cc8399e9ffe5MJ58juVe42pjM","part":{"id":"prt_e337f2b7c001qK2ne5xXSZScaz","messageID":"msg_e337f2299001wrgW0OcBlbJcbC","sessionID":"ses_1cc8399e9ffe5MJ58juVe42pjM","type":"text","text":"Implemented the fix for issue `#3596` and committed it locally.\n\nWhat changed:\n- Broadened `UBERON:0034714` `epiphyseal tract` from `innervates parietal organ` to `innervates pineal complex`.\n- Removed the generic `innervated_by obturator nerve` restriction from `UBERON:0011144` `adductor muscle of hip`.\n\nWhy:\n- The `epiphyseal tract` axiom was too narrow and inconsistent with its branching to the pineal body.\n- The `adductor muscle of hip` axiom was propagating a tetrapod-specific nerve constraint into broader vertebrate classes, matching the issue’s described unsats.\n\nValidation:\n- Checked out and checked in the edited terms with `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl`\n- Reserialized `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` with `robot convert`\n- Ran `robot reason --input src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo --reasoner ELK --output /tmp/opencode/issue-3596-reasoned.owl` successfully\n\nCommit:\n- `1da813e` `Revise taxon-constrained logical definitions`\n\nCreated and left uncommitted:\n- `ISSUE_COMMENTS.md`\n- `PR_COMMENTS.md`","time":{"start":1778980432764,"end":1778980437700}}}
